entries.body:
The ordinary workmen will come to the son of Joseph singing:

Blessed be your coming,{fn:0}

O master of workers everywhere.

The imprint of your labor is seen in the ark,{fn:1}

And in the fashioning of the tabernacle{fn:2}

Of the congregation that was for a time only!

Our whole craft praises you, who are our eternal glory.

Make for us a yoke that is light, even easy, for us to bear.{fn:3}

Establish that measure in us in which there can be no falseness. HYMNS {fn:0}

Thou, our bread, our true refreshment, never failing sweetness art;{fn:0}

He can nevermore know hunger, who is at thy banquet fed,{fn:1}

Nourishing not our fleshly nature,

but imparting lasting life.{fn:2} . . .

Every sickness now surrenders,

every listlessness departs,{fn:3}

Tongues long bound by chains of silence are unloosed and speak aright,{fn:4}

While the joyful paralytic bears his pallet through the streets.{fn:5} HYMNS 9.{fn:0}
